HEADWORD: Avile
<hw>A*vile"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>aviler</ets>, F. <ets>avilir</ets>; <ets>a</ets> (L. <ets>ad</ets>)
+ <ets>vil</ets> vile. See <er>Vile</er>.]</ety> <def>To abase or
debase; to vilify; to depreciate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Want makes us know the price of what we <qex>avile</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Avis</ent>⟦br⟧
